Touchpad Script
---------------
This is a very simple script that allows you to enable or disable your
notebook or netbook touchpad device. Very helpful if your "disable touchpad"
button does not work on linux or if you want a desktop/terminal shortcut.

## Install
Clone the repository and copy touchpad.py script to /usr/bin with execution
permissions. Try the following:

sudo mv touchpad.py /usr/bin/touchpad # moving script to user path
sudo chmod +x /usr/bin/touchpad  # giving execution permission

## Usage
touchpad ON #  turn touchpad ON
touchpad OFF # turn touchpad OFF

